---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AdBunny FAQ — Banner Monetization Questions Answered"
  description="Answers to common questions about AdBunny's AI banner monetization platform, integration, and how it works alongside your existing ad stack."
  keywords="ad monetization platform FAQ, remnant inventory questions, ad tag integration FAQ"
>
<section class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-sm">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Will AdBunny conflict with my existing ad stack?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">No. AdBunny is designed to run on remnant inventory only — the impressions your existing direct deals or header bidding partners don't fill — so it doesn't compete with your primary demand.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How long does integration take?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Typically minutes. It's a single JS tag, not a waterfall setup or SDK integration, so there's minimal engineering lift.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Do I need to configure anything after installing the tag?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">No manual configuration is required. The AI optimization layer selects the best-paying banner per impression automatically.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What ad formats does AdBunny support?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Banner formats across standard IAB sizes. Contact our team to confirm exact supported sizes for your integration.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is AdBunny suitable for small publishers, or only large ones?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Both. Because setup is a single tag with no ad-ops overhead, it works for independent sites as well as larger publishers looking to optimize remnant yield.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How does AdBunny's AI decide which banner to serve?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">For each impression, the optimization layer evaluates available demand in real time and selects the option likely to generate the highest revenue for that specific impression, rather than following a fixed, static order.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can ad networks or media buyers get access to AdBunny's inventory?</button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes — AdBunny offers programmatic access to aggregated remnant banner inventory for ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers. <a href="/advertisers" style="color:var(--c-text-secondary);font-weight:500;">See our Advertisers page</a>.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
      <a href="/advertisers" class="btn btn-outline">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
